D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-hr-startup-deel-culture-employment-regulatory-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDeel%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20had%20contacted%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20Rippling%20employees%20using%20their%20unlisted%20personal%20phone%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20it%20adds%2C%20a%20journalist%20approached%20Rippling%2C%20a%20workforce%20management%20software%20company%2C%20with%20a%20story%20claiming%20it%20may%20have%20violated%20sanctions%2C%20citing%20messages%20from%20Rippling's%20Slack%20channels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20launching%20an%20investigation%2C%20Rippling%20says%2C%20the%20company%20found%20an%20employee%20in%20Ireland%20it%20now%20says%20was%20a%20spy%20digging%20for%20corporate%20secrets%20to%20pass%20off%20to%20the%20company's%20competition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%2C%20filed%20against%20Deel%20in%20San%20Francisco%20federal%20court%2C%20says%20the%20employee%2C%20who%20oversaw%20payroll%20issues%20in%20Europe%2C%20was%20looking%20at%20Slack%20channels%20with%20%26quot%3Bno%20connection%20to%20his%20payroll%20operations%20job%20responsibilities%26quot%3B%20and%20searching%20for%20the%20term%20%26quot%3BDeel%26quot%3B%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20times%20a%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20suit%20says%20the%20man%20%E2%80%94%20who%20is%20not%20named%20in%20the%20lawsuit%20%E2%80%94%20found%20sensitive%20information%20about%20prospective%20customers%20who%20were%20looking%20to%20switch%20from%20Deel%20to%20Rippling.%20It%20adds%20that%20he%20downloaded%20a%2031-slide%20deck%20that%20explained%20Rippling's%20strategy%20for%20competing%20with%20Deel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERippling's%20leaders%20believed%20they%20found%20their%20mole.%20So%20they%20set%20up%20a%20honeypot%20operation%2C%20the%20company%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBelieving%20that%20Deel%20%26quot%3Bwas%20most%20likely%20to%20activate%20its%20spy%20if%20faced%20with%20potentially%20damaging%20press%2C%26quot%3B%20Rippling's%20general%20counsel%20emailed%20a%20legal%20letter%20to%20three%20of%20Deel's%20top%20leaders%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20says.%20The%20letter%20identified%20a%20Slack%20channel%20called%20%26quot%3B%23d-defectors%2C%26quot%3B%20on%20which%20Rippling%20employees%20discussed%20information%20that%20Deel%20would%20find%20embarrassing%20if%20it%20was%20made%20public%2C%20it%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20reality%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20says%2C%20the%20%23d-defectors%20channel%20did%20not%20exist%20until%20shortly%20before%20Rippling%20sent%20the%20letter%20to%20Deel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRather%20than%20being%20a%20gathering%20place%20for%20ex-Deel%20employees%2C%20the%20channel%20was%20set%20up%20as%20part%20of%20a%20ruse%20designed%20to%20confirm%20that%20Deel%20was%20instructing%20D.S.%20to%20search%20for%20specific%20information%20in%20Rippling's%20Slack%2C%26quot%3B%20Rippling's%20lawsuit%20says%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20person%20it%20says%20was%20%26quot%3BDeel's%20spy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeel%20%26quot%3Btook%20the%20bait%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20suit%20says.%20Just%20hours%20after%20Rippling%20sent%20the%20letter%2C%20it%20adds%2C%20this%20person%20searched%20for%20and%20accessed%20the%20channel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bsmoking%20gun%2C%26quot%3B%20Rippling%20says%20in%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20that%20Deel's%20highest%20echelon%20%E2%80%94%20or%20someone%20working%20on%20its%20behalf%20%E2%80%94%20fed%20information%20to%20that%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20course%20of%20four%20months%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20says%2C%20the%20man%20pulled%20information%20from%20Rippling's%20Slack%2C%20shared%20Google%20Drive%2C%20Salesforce%20database%2C%20and%20internal%20human%20resources%20directory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20representative%20for%20Deel%20denied%20%26quot%3Ball%20legal%20wrongdoing%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20Rippling%20was%20trying%20to%20distract%20from%20claims%20that%20it%20violated%20sanctions%20laws%2C%20which%20Rippling%20denies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWeeks%20after%20Rippling%20is%20accused%20of%20violating%20sanctions%20law%20in%20Russia%20and%20seeding%20falsehoods%20about%20Deel%2C%20Rippling%20is%20trying%20to%20shift%20the%20narrative%20with%20these%20sensationalized%20claims%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Deel%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BWe%20deny%20all%20legal%20wrongdoing%20and%20look%20forward%20to%20asserting%20our%20counterclaims.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22240361e8-598e-480d-b8ec-4a312b43245c%5C%22%3EA%20tech%20rivalry%20for%20the%20ages%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERippling's%20lawsuit%2C%20which%20demands%20a%20jury%20trial%2C%20marks%20a%20fiery%20escalation%20in%20its%20rivalry%20with%20Deel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFounded%20in%202016%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparker-conrad-rippling-143-million-cloud-hr-zenefits-2020-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EParker%20Conrad%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20mainstay%20of%20the%20workforce%20software%20market%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frippling-hr-startup-growth-parker-conrad-eisar-lipkovitz%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERippling%20creates%20tools%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20streamline%20a%20company's%20back%20office.%20It%20launched%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20gathering%20all%20of%20a%20customer's%20data%20about%20its%20employees%20and%20placing%20it%20in%20one%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeel%20came%20onto%20the%20scene%20with%20a%20different%20proposition.%20In%202019%2C%20the%20company%20functioned%20as%20an%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-hr-startup-deel-culture-employment-regulatory-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemployer%20of%20record%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20for%20companies%2C%20allowing%20its%20customers%20to%20hire%20globally%20without%20having%20to%20worry%20about%20compliance%20regulations%20in%20different%20countries.%20Over%20time%2C%20Deel%2C%20led%20by%20its%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%2C%20Alex%20Bouaziz%2C%20bolted%20a%20wider%20variety%20of%20products%20onto%20its%20system%2C%20building%20them%20in-house%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeel-ceo-acquisition-strategy-alex-bouaziz-assemble-hr-tech-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuying%20up%20small%20players%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20payroll%20and%20IT.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20firms%20now%20go%20head-to-head%20in%20the%20workforce%20software%20market%2C%20raising%20bigger%20and%20faster%20rounds%20of%20funding%20to%20expand%20their%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20competition%20has%20often%20unfolded%20in%20the%20public%20eye.%20This%20past%20spring%2C%20when%20Rippling%20held%20a%20tender%20offer%2C%20which%20refers%20to%20the%20sale%20of%20a%20shareholder's%20stock%20in%20a%20company%2C%20the%20company%20barred%20former%20employees%20who%20work%20for%20its%20competitors%2C%20including%20Deel%2C%20from%20cashing%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20a%20class%20action%20complaint%20alleged%20that%20Deel%20lacked%20the%20proper%20licenses%20to%20process%20payments%20for%20a%20company%20accused%20of%20operating%20a%20Ponzi%20scheme%20but%20that%20it%20did%20so%20anyway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plaintiff's%20lawyer%2C%20Thomas%20Grady%2C%20has%20been%20reported%20to%20be%20an%20investor%20in%20Rippling.%20In%20a%20motion%20to%20dismiss%2C%20Deel%20denied%20any%20wrongdoing%20and%20rejected%20the%20complaint%20as%20a%20feckless%20attack%20by%20its%20biggest%20competitor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2248b02214-757c-4443-80ed-80e3cf97d668%5C%22%3EA%20court%20order%20and%20a%20flushing%20toilet%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERippling%20says%20it%20picked%20up%20the%20trail%20of%20the%20person%20it%20alleges%20was%20a%20corporate%20spy%20partly%20by%20looking%20at%20his%20Slack%20activity.%20The%20employee%2C%20who%20joined%20Rippling%20in%202023%2C%20had%20rarely%20used%20the%20%26quot%3Bpreview%26quot%3B%20function%20on%20Slack%2C%20which%20allows%20users%20to%20view%20a%20channel's%20contents%20without%20notifying%20colleagues%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20November%2C%20the%20suit%20says%2C%20the%20employee%20started%20previewing%20dozens%20of%20channels%20a%20month%2C%20sometimes%20peeking%20at%20particular%20channels%20more%20than%20100%20times%20each%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20channels%20were%20dedicated%20to%20information%20about%20Rippling's%20services%20and%20software%20sales%2C%20as%20well%20as%20information%20about%20competitors%20like%20Deel%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERippling's%20suit%20says%20the%20employee's%20browser%20and%20email%20history%20indicate%20he%20may%20have%20also%20met%20with%20Bouaziz%20and%20Deel's%20global%20head%20of%20expansion%2C%20Olivier%20Elbaz%2C%20in%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20after%20the%20honeypot%20operation%2C%20Rippling%20sought%20a%20court%20order%20in%20Ireland%20to%20seize%20and%20inspect%20the%20employee's%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20court-appointed%20solicitor%20served%20the%20employee%20with%20the%20order%20at%20Rippling's%20Dublin%20office%2C%20the%20suit%20says%2C%20the%20employee%20said%20his%20phone%20was%20in%20a%20bag%20on%20another%20floor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20lie%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20alleges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20bag%20only%20contained%20a%20notebook.%20It%20held%20no%20mobile%20device%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20suit%20says%20the%20man%20then%20went%20to%20the%20bathroom%20and%20locked%20the%20door%2C%20%26quot%3Bdespite%20the%20independent%20solicitor's%20repeated%20warnings%20that%20these%20actions%20were%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20court%20order.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20willing%20to%20take%20that%20risk%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20employee%20said%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20employee%20%26quot%3Bthen%20stormed%20out%20of%20the%20office%20and%20fled%20the%20scene%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20says.%3C%2Fp%