E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20both%20been%20on%20deployments.%20We're%20not%20surprised%20when%20deployments%20get%20changed%2C%26quot%3B%20Williams%20said%20in%20a%20September%20call%20with%20journalists.%20%26quot%3BOur%20families%20are%20used%20to%20that%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilliams%20was%20born%20in%20Ohio%20and%20grew%20up%20in%20Needham%2C%20Massachusetts.%20She%20became%20a%20Naval%20aviator%20in%201989%20and%20made%20a%20series%20of%20deployments%20overseas%20as%20part%20of%20a%20helicopter%20combat%20support%20unit%2C%20including%20for%20Operation%20Desert%20Shield%20and%20Operation%20Provide%20Comfort%20in%20the%20Persian%20Gulf.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20ran%20a%20detachment%20for%20Hurricane%20Andrew%20relief%20in%20Miami%20in%201992%2C%20then%20spent%20a%20few%20years%20conducting%20rotary%20aircraft%20test%20flights%20before%20becoming%20an%20instructor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENASA%20selected%20Williams%20to%20be%20an%20astronaut%20in%201998%2C%20while%20she%20was%20deployed%20on%20the%20USS%20Saipan.%20She%20began%20training%20two%20months%20later.%20Her%20first%20gig%20at%20NASA%20was%20going%20to%20Moscow%20to%20work%20with%20Russia's%20space%20agency%20on%20its%20piece%20of%20the%20International%20Space%20Station.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20wide-ranging%20time%20at%20NASA%2C%20Williams%20has%20also%20spent%20nine%20days%20living%20in%20an%20underwater%20habitat%20and%20flown%20two%20previous%20missions%20totaling%20322%20days%20on%20the%20International%20Space%20Station.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22astronaut%20in%20white%20spacesuit%20and%20helmet%20reflecting%20earth%20floating%20near%20a%20white%20robotic%20arm%20with%20space%20station%20solar%20panel%20arrays%20in%20the%20background%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d4ad8f69253ccddf995fe3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWilliams%20conducts%20a%20spacewalk%2C%20attached%20to%20a%20robotic%20arm%20of%20the%20space%20station.%3Cp%3EGRK%2FNASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20in%20the%20September%20call%20what%20she%20missed%20about%20Earth%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bof%20course%2C%20the%20things%20that%20we%20always%20miss%3A%20our%20families.%20I%20miss%20my%20two%20dogs%2C%20I%20miss%20my%20friends.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20and%20her%20dogs%20live%20with%20her%20husband%2C%20Michael%2C%20and%20the%20couple%20enjoy%20some%20highly%20technical%20hobbies%3A%20working%20on%20houses%2C%20cars%2C%20and%20airplanes%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229488d3cb-da44-446c-b472-9e23bd86eb83%5C%22%3EWho%20is%20Barry%20'Butch'%20Wilmore%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWilmore%20is%20a%20retired%20US%20Navy%20captain%2C%20having%20spent%20the%20first%20part%20of%20his%20career%20flying%20tactical%20jets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20completed%208%2C000%20flight%20hours%2C%20663%20landings%20on%20an%20aircraft%20carrier%2C%20and%20four%20operational%20deployments.%20During%20Operation%20Desert%20Storm%2C%20he%20carried%20out%2021%20combat%20missions%20from%20the%20flight%20deck%20of%20the%20USS%20Kennedy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20spent%20some%20time%20as%20a%20flight%20instructor%20at%20Edwards%20Air%20Force%20Base%2C%20California%2C%20before%20NASA%20selected%20him%20as%20an%20astronaut%20in%202000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222250%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Butch%20Wilmore%20looking%20through%20a%20camera%20he's%20pointing%20to%20a%20rectangular%20window%20inside%20the%20space%20station%20looking%20out%20on%20blue%20cloudy%20earth%20below%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b3dc72b4912df3ae19cf0f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EButch%20Wilmore%20photographs%20Earth%20landmarks%20from%20the%20space%20station's%20cupola.%3Cp%3ENASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20previously%20flown%20two%20NASA%20missions%3A%20an%2011-day%20mission%20on%20the%20Space%20Shuttle%20Atlantis%20in%202009%20and%20a%20shift%20of%20167%20days%20on%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20in%202014%20and%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilmore%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20Deanna%2C%20are%20originally%20from%20Tennessee.%20Now%2C%20the%20couple%20and%20their%20two%20daughters%2C%20Daryn%20and%20Logan%2C%20live%20in%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20September%20call%2C%20Wilmore%20cited%20a%20Bible%20verse%20about%20gaining%20strength%20from%20adversity%20as%20%26quot%3Bhow%20I%20feel%20about%20all%20of%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20later%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20deal%20with%20all%20types%20of%20difficulties%20in%20all%20types%20of%20situations%20and%20it%20builds%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20fortitude%20and%20it%20builds%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20character.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsunita-williams-butch-wilmore-nasa-astronauts-stuck-space-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742230205000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d4ae10585f1dff88b24488%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsunita-williams-butch-wilmore-nasa-astronauts-stuck-space-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Butch%20Wilmore%20and%20Sunita%20Williams%20will%20finally%20return%20to%20Earth%20after%20nine%20months%20'stuck'%20in%20space.%20The%20NASA%20astronauts%20are%20awaiting%20rescue%20by%20SpaceX.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mmcfalljohnsen%40businessinsider.com%20(Morgan%20McFall-Johnsen)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A140%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsunita-williams-butch-wilmore-nasa-astronauts-stuck-space-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Windows%20smashed%20in%20pub%20belonging%20to%20owner%20of%20nightclub%20where