ther.%20One%20film%20had%20Khan%20playing%20a%20village%20farmer%2C%20hardly%20the%20stuff%20of%20blockbusters.%20In%20the%20other%2C%20he%20shared%20the%20frame%20with%20two%20relatively%20lesser%20known%20faces.%20Nothing%20about%20these%20projects%20suggested%20the%20seismic%20shift%20they%20were%20about%20to%20trigger.%20Perhaps%20everyone%20misjudged.%20Or%20worse%2C%20they%20failed%20to%20see%20what%20Khan%20had%20already%20glimpsed.%20Maybe%20they%20weren't%20paying%20attention.%20Maybe%20they%20couldn't%20see%20him%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Slide%20Till%202001%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20back%20then%2C%20Khan%20was%20just%20another%20actor%20whose%20filmography%20offered%20little%20to%20linger%20on%2C%20let%20alone%20celebrate.%20Yes%2C%20his%20magnetic%20debut%20in%20%3Cem%3EQayamat%20Se%20Qayamat%20Tak%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehad%20made%20him%20a%20heartthrob%2C%20but%20what%20followed%20was%20a%20stretch%20of%20misfires%20and%20mediocrity.%20For%20every%20%3Cem%3ERangeela%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESarfarosh%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20there%20was%20a%20%3Cem%3EMela%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20a%20%3Cem%3EMann%20%3C%2Fem%3Edragging%20him%20back%20to%20the%20ordinary.%20He%20flirted%20with%20fresher%2C%20independent%20voices%20(Aditya%20Bhattacharya%2C%20Ram%20Gopal%20Varma%2C%20Deepa%20Mehta)%2C%20but%20more%20often%2C%20he%20leaned%20on%20the%20safety%20net%20of%20big-league%20filmmakers%20(Mahesh%20Bhatt%2C%20Yash%20Chopra%2C%20Inder%20Kumar).%20Occasionally%2C%20he%20strayed%20into%20something%20different%2C%20but%20his%20instincts%20kept%20circling%20back%20to%20familiar%2C%20romantic%20terrain.%20Even%20at%20the%20box%20office%2C%20his%20shine%20had%20faded.%20His%20last%20true%20blockbuster%2C%20%3Cem%3ERaja%20Hindustani%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20was%20already%20five%20years%20behind%20him.%20By%202001%2C%20the%20odds%20and%20perceptions%20were%20stacked%20against%20him.%20It%20seemed%20like%20he%20had%20everything%20to%20lose%20and%20almost%20nothing%20to%20gain.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20If%20there's%20one%20actor%20who%20refuses%20to%20be%20pinned%20down%2C%20who%20defies%2C%20eludes%2C%20and%20shatters%20expectations%2C%20it's%20Khan.%20In%202001%2C%20he%20arrived%20twice%2C%20just%20two%20months%20apart%2C%20and%20each%20time%2C%20he%20tore%20through%20the%20rules%20of%20commercial%20Hindi%20cinema.%20He%20didn't%20just%20reshape%20the%20language%20of%20storytelling%3B%20he%20redefined%20the%20moment%2C%20and%20in%20the%20process%2C%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Cult%20Of%20%3Cem%3ELagaan%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20was%20%3Cem%3ELagaan%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0a%20leap%20so%20improbable%2C%20it%20feels%20like%20myth.%20In%20retrospect%2C%20it%20seems%20destined%20for%20glory.%20After%20all%2C%20a%20perfect%20fusion%20of%20cinema%20and%20cricket%2C%20India's%20twin%20obsessions.%20How%20could%20it%20fail%3F%20But%20to%20read%20it%20only%20through%20hindsight%20is%20to%20miss%20its%20razor's%20edge.%20Its%20screenplay%20was%20a%20high-wire%20act%2C%20so%20delicate%2C%20so%20radical%2C%20that%20it%20was%20more%20likely%20to%20collapse%20under%20its%20own%20ambition%20than%20to%20succeed.%20And%20then%2C%20there%20was%20%3Cem%3EDil%20Chahta%20Hai%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20so%20fresh%2C%20so%20disarmingly%20modern%2C%20that%20you%20had%20to%20experience%20it%20to%20believe%20it.%20Today%2C%20it%20might%20seem%20like%20an%20effortless%20breeze%3B%20a%20buddy%20film%20about%20love%20and%20friendship.%20But%20back%20then%2C%20it%20was%20nothing%20less%20than%20a%20rebellion.%20Its%20form%2C%20its%20content%2C%20its%20gaze%2C%20everything%20about%20it%20broke%20from%20the%20past.%20Only%20from%20the%20safe%20distance%20of%20retrospect%20does%20its%20triumph%20feel%20certain.%20In%20reality%2C%20few%20films%20have%20ever%20altered%20the%20landscape%20the%20way%20it%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20since%20then%2C%20few%20actors%20have%20altered%20the%20medium%20the%20way%20Khan%20has.%20Almost%20overnight%2C%20his%20name%20was%20everywhere%3A%20on%20every%20screen%2C%20on%20everyone's%20lips.%20It%20felt%20as%20if%20he%20had%20emerged%20from%20nowhere%20and%20suddenly%20had%20it%20all.%20Next%20to%20him%2C%20the%20other%20Khans%20(Shah%20Rukh%20and%20Salman)%20seemed%20to%20blur%20into%20the%20background.%20With%20every%20new%20role%2C%20he%20appeared%20to%20shed%20his%20old%20self%20and%20become%20someone%20else%20entirely.%20He%20was%20no%20longer%20just%20any%20other%20actor%3A%20he%20was%20the%20most%20versatile%2C%20the%20most%20cerebral%2C%20and%20perhaps%2C%20the%20most%20secure.%20It%20didn't%20matter%20if%20he%20played%20second%20fiddle.%20It%20didn't%20matter%20if%20the%20director%20he%20worked%20with%20had%20never%20tasted%20success.%20What%20mattered%20was%20the%20pursuit%20of%20telling%20something%20new%2C%20something%20urgent.%20He%20wanted%20to%20tell%20stories%20that%20cut%20deeper%2C%20to%20stretch%20the%20language%20of%20cinema%2C%20to%20move%20audiences%20in%20ways%20they%20hadn't%20been%20before.%20In%20an%20industry%20that%20clings%20to%20the%20familiar%2C%20he%20became%20a%20beacon%20for%20risk.%20In%20a%20world%20where%20most%20play%20the%20same%20character%20on%20repeat%2C%20he%20chose%20to%20be%20a%20chameleon%3B%20always%20shifting%2C%20always%20one%20step%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20The%20Up%20And%20Up%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMangal%20Pandey%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3ERang%20De%20Basanti%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EFanaa%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EGhajini%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3E3%20Idiots%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EDhobi%20Ghat%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3ETalaash%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20list%20really%20goes%20on.%20With%20each%20film%2C%20he%20unlocked%20new%20shades%20of%20himself%2C%20stretching%20his%20range%2C%20deepening%20his%20craft.%20Each%20role%20didn't%20just%20make%20him%20a%20household%20name%20(if%20he%20wasn't%20one%20already)%2C%20it%20cemented%20his%20place%20as%20a%20cultural%20obsession.%20The%20audience%20wasn't%20just%20watching%20him%20anymore%3B%20they%20were%20waiting%20for%20him.%20Every%20year%2C%20they%20opened%20their%20hearts%20and%20their%20wallets%2C%20flocking%20to%20theatres%20in%20numbers%20that%20only%20grew%20larger.%20Inevitably%2C%20he%20became%20the%20most%20bankable%2C%20the%20most%20profitable.%20His%20films%20didn't%20just%20reshape%20cinema%3B%20they%20rewrote%20the%20business%20itself.%20%3Cem%3EGhajini%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewas%20the%20first%20Bollywood%20film%20to%20net%20Rs%20100%20crore%20in%20the%20domestic%20market.%20%3Cem%3E3%20Idiots%3C%2Fem%3E%20pushed%20the%20boundary%20to%20200%20crore.%20%3Cem%3EPK%3C%2Fem%3E%20shattered%20it%20again%20with%20Rs%20300%20crore.%20The%20records%20kept%20falling%2C%20and%20the%20list%20again%20kept%20growing.%20Perhaps%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20he%20became%20the%20rarest%20figure%20in%20Hindi%20cinema%3A%20someone%20who%20effortlessly%20married%20art%20with%20commerce%2C%20and%20made%20both%20feel%20inseparable.%20Perhaps%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20he%20was%20no%20longer%20just%20an%20actor%20who%20took%20risks%2C%20he%20was%20a%20star%20who%20could%20act.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20that's%20the%20thing%20about%20stardom%3A%20it%20demands%20to%20be%20the%20centre%20of%20everything.%20No%20matter%20how%20much%20Khan%20insists%20he%20is%20an%20actor%20first%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20much%20the%20world%20admires%20the%20actor%20in%20him%2C%20he%20remains%E2%80%A6a%20star.%20And%20stars%2C%20by%20their%20very%20nature%2C%20cannot%20escape%20gravity%E2%80%94they%20pull%20everything%20towards%20themselves.%20What%20followed%20in%20his%20filmography%20is%20fascinating.%20On%20the%20surface%2C%20he%20seemed%20to%20continue%20the%20path%20he%20had%20carved%20for%20over%20a%20decade%3A%20taking%20risks%2C%20choosing%20stories%20that%20defied%20formula.%20But%20quietly%2C%20almost%20imperceptibly%2C%20he%20began%20to%20shape%20a%20formula%20out%20of%20what%20once%20felt%20formless.%20His%20films%20gave%20room%20for%20others%20to%20shine%20but%20only%20until%20he%20arrived.%20They%20weren't%20about%20him%2C%20until%2C%20suddenly%2C%20they%20were.%20And%20once%20he%20stepped%20into%20the%20frame%2C%20there%20was%20no%20looking%20anywhere%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Star%20In%20The%20Shadows%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETake%20films%20like%3Cem%3E%20Dangal%20%3C%2Fem%3Eor%20%3Cem%3ESecret%20Superstar%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Both%20widely%20acclaimed%2C%20both%20deeply%20loved%2C%20both%20massively%20successful.%20On%20the%20surface%2C%20these%20are%20stories%20where%20Khan%20steps%20back%2C%20allowing%20other%20characters%20to%20take%20centre%20stage.%20And%20yet%2C%20their%20journey%20toward%20fulfilment%20always%20circles%20back%20to%20him.%20In%20both%20films%2C%20his%20heroism%20is%20amplified%20by%20caricatured%20villains%2C%20who%20are%20conveniently%20one-note%20and%20easy%20to%20hate%2C%20ensuring%20that%20his%20presence%20remains%20the%20focal%20point.%20The%20same%20holds%20true%20for%20%3Cem%3ETaare%20Zameen%20Par%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3E3%20Idiots%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20even%20%3Cem%3EPK%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Time%20and%20again%2C%20he%20becomes%20the%20voice%20of%20reason%2C%20the%20fountain%20of%20wisdom%2C%20the%20man%20who%20can%20do%20no%20wrong.%20The%20world%20around%20him%20is%20always%20in%20need%20of%20saving%2C%20and%20he%20is%20always%20the%20saviour.%20In%20this%20sense%2C%20Khan%2C%20despite%20his%20reputation%20as%20a%20rule-breaker%2C%20mirrors%20every%20other%20Bollywood%20star%3A%20upright%2C%20invincible%2C%20indispensable.%20No%20matter%20how%20unconventional%20his%20films%20may%20appear%2C%20they%20remain%2C%20at%20their%20heart%2C%20star%20vehicles.%20They%20are%20subtly%20designed%20to%20magnify%20his%20presence%2C%20to%20orbit%20his%20image%2C%20and%20consequently%2C%20to%20serve%20his%20myth.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20myth%20of%20the%20perfectionist.%20A%20label%20casually%20tossed%20his%20way%2C%20embraced%20by%20the%20media%20and%20audience%20alike.%20But%20perhaps%20he%20took%20it%20too%20seriously.%20Perhaps%20it%20now%20shapes%20the%20way%20he%20makes%20his%20films%E2%80%94subtly%20but%20unmistakably.%20Because%20by%20now%2C%20this%20pattern%20is%20hard%20to%20miss.%20Yet%2C%20there's%20another%20pattern%20worth%20noting%3A%20whenever%20Khan%20positions%20himself%20as%20the%20unambiguous%20hero%2C%20the%20cracks%20begin%20to%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Awkwardness%20Of%20%3Cem%3EGhajini%3C%2Fem%3E%20And%20%3Cem%3EDhoom%203%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20first%20became%20apparent%20in%20%3Cem%3EGhajini%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Even%20then%20(and%20more%20so%20now)%20his%20performance%20felt%20almost%20unwatchable.%20But%20back%20then%2C%20the%20film%20itself%20was%20such%20a%20novelty%20for%20mainstream%20audiences%20(never%20mind%20that%20it%20borrowed%20liberally%20from%20Christopher%20Nolan's%20%3Cem%3EMemento%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20was%20a%20remake%20of%20a%20Tamil%20blockbuster)%20that%20few%20looked%20past%20its%20surface.%20Since%20then%2C%20whenever%20Khan%20has%20tried%20to%20lead%20a%20conventional%2C%20hero-driven%20spectacle%2C%20the%20strain%20has%20only%20grown%20harder%20to%20ignore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESure%2C%20%3Cem%3EDhoom%203%20%3C%2Fem%3Eraked%20in%20bizarre%20numbers%2C%20but%20watching%20Khan%20lead%20a%20franchise%20built%20on%20sheer%20charisma%20and%20swagger%20felt%20oddly%20out%20of%20place.%20It%20felt%20like%20a%20guest%20overstaying%20a%20party%20that%20was%20never%20meant%20for%20them.%20The%20discomfort%20only%20deepened%20with%20%3Cem%3EThugs%20of%20Hindostan%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20pointless%20period%20actioner%20where%20the%20cracks%20were%20too%20wide%20to%20ignore.%20This%20time%2C%20the%20audience%20was%20sharp%20enough%20to%20notice%2C%20and%20the%20film%20collapsed%20under%20its%20own%20weight.%20It%20was%20Khan's%20first%20true%20disaster%20since%20his%20golden%20streak%20began%20in%202001.%20What%20followed%20was%20an%20even%20sharper%20descent.%20%3Cem%3ELaal%20Singh%20Chaddha%3C%2Fem%3E%20became%20a%20lightning%20rod%20for%20mockery.%20His%20performance%3A%20broad%2C%20mannered%2C%20almost%20cartoonish%2C%20was%20ridiculed%20with%20rare%20ferocity.%20Sure%2C%20an%20argument%20can%20be%20made%20(and%20Khan%20himself%20has%20said%20this)%20that%20both%20%3Cem%3EThugs%20of%20Hindostan%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3ELaal%20Singh%20Chaddha%3C%2Fem%3E%20failed%20because%20they%20were%20simply%20shoddy%20films.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20Expect%20Too%20Much%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20another%2C%20more%20unsettling%20argument%3A%20the%20backlash%2C%20particularly%20against%20%3Cem%3ELaal%20Singh%20Chaddha%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20wasn't%20just%20about%20false%20notes%20in%20his%20performance.%20It%20was%20the%20sheer%20disbelief%20that%20a%20so-called%20%E2%80%98perfectionist'%20could%20stumble%20so%20spectacularly.%20Maybe%20then%20the%20real%20issue%20isn't%20just%20the%20films%20themselves%E2%80%94it's%20us.%20We%20expect%20every%20%E2%80%9CAamir%20Khan%20project%E2%80%9D%20to%20carry%20weight%2C%20to%20deliver%20a%20message%2C%20to%20be%20a%20cultural%20event.%20Maybe%20we've%20grown%20incapable%20of%20accepting%20his%20films%20as%20just%20stories%3B%20as%20pure%20entertainment.%20We%20expect%20every%20character%20he%20portrays%20to%20align%20with%20the%20values%20associated%20with%20his%20brand%3A%20intelligence%2C%20morality%2C%20and%20social%20consciousness.%20Perhaps%20that's%20why%20a%20performance%20like%20%3Cem%3ETalaash%20%3C%2Fem%3Erarely%20finds%20space%20in%20popular%20discourse.%20Simply%20because%20it%20doesn't%20serve%20his%20image.%20It%20doesn't%20seek%20to%20reassure%20or%20inspire.%20It%20just%20lets%20him%20be%20flawed%2C%20broken%2C%20and%20human.%20Indeed%2C%20it's%20an%20impossible%20paradox%E2%80%94one%20where%20Khan%2C%20ironically%2C%20has%20become%20like%20any%20other%20major%20star%20in%20India%3A%20bound%20by%20the%20expectations%20of%20his%20fan%20base.%20Indeed%2C%20it's%20a%20curious%20evolution%E2%80%94an%20actor%20who%20once%20took%20pride%20in%20doing%20things%20differently%20now%20finds%20himself%20pigeonholed%20in%20a%20cage%20of%20his%20own%20making.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWill%20There%20Be%20A%20Second%20Coming%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%202025%20now.%20Khan%20is%2060%20today.%20He%20has%20a%20film%20on%20the%20horizon.%20But%20the%20landscape%20isn't%20what%20it%20used%20to%20be.%20The%20rules%20have%20changed%20since%20he%20last%20stood%20in%20the%20spotlight.%20The%20very%20genres%20he%20once%20championed%20are%20now%20relegated%20to%20the%20world%20of%20OTT.%20It's%20said%20only%20larger-than-life%20action%20(or%20horror)%20spectacles%20can%20draw%20audiences.%20His%20is%20a%20breezy%2C%20message-driven%20comedy.%20Remakes%2C%20they%20say%2C%20are%20a%20dying%20breed.%20His%20is%20an%20adaptation%20of%20a%20Spanish%20film.%20Nothing%20about%20it%20suggests%20it%20should%20work.%20But%20then%20again%2C%20nothing%20in%202001%20did%20either.%20Maybe%20everyone%20is%20misjudging%20him.%20Or%20worse%2C%20maybe%20he's%20failing%20to%20see%20what%20he%20once%20was.%20Maybe%20they're%20still%20not%20paying%20attention.%20Because%20maybe%E2%80%94just%20like%20them%E2%80%94he%2C%20too%2C%20can't%20see%20that%20he's%20always%20been%20a%20perfectionist%20second%2C%20and%20a%20trailblazer%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Anas%20Arif%20is%20a%20film%20writer%20and%20a%20media%20graduate%20from%20AJKMCRC%2C%20Jamia%20Millia%20Islamia)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742209380000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2Fkpdu78b_aamir-khan_625x300_17_March_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopin